President Biden and Prime Minister Modi gave speeches during a dinner at Prime Minister Modi's Washington home. President Biden highlighted the strong friendship between the United States and India and the importance of their partnership in making the world a safer place. He also praised the contributions of Indian Americans to various fields in the United States. Prime Minister Modi expressed gratitude for the warm hospitality and friendship extended by President Biden and emphasized the values of democracy and diversity shared by both countries. He also mentioned the growing cultural exchange between India and the United States, including the popularity of cricket in the US. Both leaders offered toasts to the strong bonds of friendship between India and the United States.